<subSubSection id="678765282007E359FF3BBFFBFCCEFE45" lastPageId="26" lastPageNumber="103" pageId="25" pageNumber="102" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="2F2236A32007E359FF3BBFFBFC1FFECE" blockId="25.[242,1474,1791,1850]" lastBlockId="26.[212,1444,266,463]" lastPageId="26" lastPageNumber="103" pageId="25" pageNumber="102">
REMARKS. — This species was formerly placed in 
<taxonomicName id="E89D4D202007E35AFCF9BE05FC71F892" authorityName="Stewart" authorityYear="1930" box="[816,953,1793,1816]" class="Bivalvia" family="Pectinidae" genus="Delectopecten" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pectinida" pageId="25" pageNumber="102" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1DE9EAB12007E35AFCF9BE05FC71F892" box="[816,953,1793,1816]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="102">Delectopecten</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation id="4B0C4B522007E35AFC35BFFBFB5EF89D" author="DIJKSTRA H. H." box="[1020,1174,1791,1815]" pageId="25" pageNumber="102" pagination="348 - 373" refId="ref26877" refString="DIJKSTRA H. H. 2001. - Bathyal Pectinoidea (Bivalvia: Propeamussiidae, Lawrence: 348 - 373." type="book chapter" year="2001">Dijkstra 2001</bibRefCitation>
). However, examination of Pliocene material of 
<taxonomicName id="E89D4D202007E35AFE1BBE26FDAAF8B0" authorityName="Seguenza" authorityYear="1877" box="[466,610,1826,1850]" class="Bivalvia" family="Pectinidae" genus="Ciclopecten" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pectinida" pageId="25" pageNumber="102" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="peloritanus">
<emphasis id="1DE9EAB12007E35AFE1BBE26FDAAF8B0" box="[466,610,1826,1850]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="102">C. peloritanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the 
<typeStatus id="F02688012007E35AFD55BE26FD02F8B0" box="[668,714,1826,1850]" pageId="25" pageNumber="102">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName id="E89D4D202007E35AFC8CBE27FC7FF8B0" authorityName="Seguenza" authorityYear="1877" box="[837,951,1827,1850]" class="Bivalvia" family="Pectinidae" genus="Ciclopecten" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pectinida" pageId="25" pageNumber="102" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1DE9EAB12007E35AFC8CBE27FC7FF8B0" box="[837,951,1827,1850]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="102">Ciclopecten</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from 
<collectingCountry id="578A76332007E35AFBC8BE26FBF9F8B0" box="[1025,1073,1826,1850]" name="Italy" pageId="25" pageNumber="102">Italy</collectingCountry>
, indicates that the present species is morphologically closer to 
<taxonomicName id="E89D4D202004E359FE21B80FFD92FEA8" authorityName="Seguenza" authorityYear="1877" box="[488,602,267,290]" class="Bivalvia" family="Pectinidae" genus="Ciclopecten" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pectinida" pageId="26" pageNumber="103" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1DE9EAB12004E359FE21B80FFD92FEA8" box="[488,602,267,290]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="103">Ciclopecten</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
than to 
<emphasis id="1DE9EAB12004E359FD7BB80FFC8AFEA8" box="[690,834,267,290]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="103">
<taxonomicName id="E89D4D202004E359FD7BB80FFCF6FEA8" authorityName="Stewart" authorityYear="1930" box="[690,830,267,290]" class="Bivalvia" family="Pectinidae" genus="Delectopecten" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pectinida" pageId="26" pageNumber="103" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">Delectopecten</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
It has similar commarginal undulations and antimarginal microsculpture. For a description of 
<taxonomicName id="E89D4D202004E359FD90B829FD10FECF" baseAuthorityName="Bavay" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[601,728,301,325]" class="Bivalvia" family="Pectinidae" genus="Ciclopecten" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pectinida" pageId="26" pageNumber="103" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="fluctuatus">
<emphasis id="1DE9EAB12004E359FD90B829FD10FECF" box="[601,728,301,325]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="103">C. fluctuatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
see 
<bibRefCitation id="4B0C4B522004E359FCCFB829FC1BFECE" author="DIJKSTRA H. H." box="[774,979,300,325]" pageId="26" pageNumber="103" pagination="3 - 25" refId="ref26691" refString="DIJKSTRA H. H. 1995. - Bathyal Pectinoidea (Bivalvia: Propeamussiidae: regions. Nature and Culture 1: 3 - 25. Tokyo." type="journal article" year="1995">Dijkstra (1995: 51)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2F2236A32004E359FF3BB84BFCCEFE45" blockId="26.[212,1444,266,463]" pageId="26" pageNumber="103">
The present specimen from the 
<collectingRegion id="ED59F8412004E359FD8AB854FD7EFEED" box="[579,694,336,359]" country="French Polynesia" name="Iles Marquises" pageId="26" pageNumber="103">Marquesas</collectingRegion>
is similar to the 
<typeStatus id="F02688012004E359FCACB84BFC0BFEED" box="[869,963,335,359]" pageId="26" pageNumber="103">holotype</typeStatus>
from the Andaman Sea, but differs slightly in size (
<quantity id="E8659B462004E359FEC3B876FE9EFE03" box="[266,342,370,394]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="26" pageNumber="103" unit="mm" value="15.0">15 mm</quantity>
in height, 
<typeStatus id="F02688012004E359FE0AB876FDE9FE00" box="[451,545,370,394]" pageId="26" pageNumber="103">holotype</typeStatus>
<quantity id="E8659B462004E359FDEFB876FDBCFE00" box="[550,628,370,394]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="26" pageNumber="103" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 mm</quantity>
), sculpture of the left valve (fine radial sculpture, 
<typeStatus id="F02688012004E359FBB1B876FB1EFE00" box="[1144,1238,370,394]" pageId="26" pageNumber="103">holotype</typeStatus>
somewhat coarser) and the presence of delicate commarginal sculpture (nearly lacking in 
<typeStatus id="F02688012004E359FC74B891FBE8FE27" box="[957,1056,405,429]" pageId="26" pageNumber="103">holotype</typeStatus>
). However, intermediate variants are also known (MNHN). Other characters are identical.
</paragraph>
